1
00:00:03,571 --> 00:00:05,170
       [ Computer beeps ]       

2
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:06,972
             -Hello?            
          -Hi, Peridot.         

3
00:00:06,974 --> 00:00:08,540
Steven, can you hear me?        

4
00:00:08,542 --> 00:00:10,676
        -I-I can hear y--       
       -Can you hear me?!       

5
00:00:10,678 --> 00:00:12,444
         -I can hear y--        
          -[ Grumbles ]         

6
00:00:12,446 --> 00:00:13,812
      How do I                  
work this stupid thing?         

7
00:00:13,814 --> 00:00:14,813
        Ahh!                    

8
00:00:14,815 --> 00:00:15,848
       Steven?                  

9
00:00:15,850 --> 00:00:16,648
                Hi, Peridot.    

10
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:19,685
       Steven!                  
     [ Laughs ]                 

11
00:00:19,687 --> 00:00:22,554
       Behold                   
my resourceful genius!          

12
00:00:22,556 --> 00:00:24,957
I figured out how to            
get Wi-Fi in the barn.          

13
00:00:24,959 --> 00:00:26,558
   The connection               
is fast enough to stream        

14
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:31,030
"Camp Pining Hearts"            
  in all 1,080 p's.             

15
00:00:31,032 --> 00:00:34,833
It took me a while, but let me  
tell you how I did it.          

16
00:00:34,835 --> 00:00:36,335
   -So, I had to go through...  
       [ Computer beeps ]       

17
00:00:36,337 --> 00:00:37,736
                  Peridot?      

18
00:00:37,738 --> 00:00:40,839
So, there I was, face to face   
with one of those big --        

19
00:00:40,841 --> 00:00:43,575
       [ Static squeals ]       
  -Peridot, you're breaking up. 

20
00:00:43,577 --> 00:00:45,411
...running for my life          
with nothing but a --           

21
00:00:45,413 --> 00:00:47,246
       [ Static squeals ]       
      -And then it bit me!      

22
00:00:47,248 --> 00:00:50,516
       [ Computer beeps ]       
And now the Wi-Fi works         
 perfectly.                     

23
00:00:50,518 --> 00:00:52,384
What did you do today?          

24
00:00:52,386 --> 00:00:54,820
                  I learned     
               how to do this.  

25
00:00:54,822 --> 00:00:56,488
        What?                   

26
00:00:56,490 --> 00:00:58,524
Lapis, get over here.           

27
00:00:58,526 --> 00:00:59,925
               Is that Steven?  

28
00:00:59,927 --> 00:01:02,761
              -Yes.             
 -Oh, no! Steven, what happened?

29
00:01:02,763 --> 00:01:04,830
    Oh, you guys, it's fine.    
         It's just a --         

30
00:01:04,832 --> 00:01:06,498
                 How did he     
           get trapped in there?

31
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:07,833
               Why aren't you   
              doing something?  

32
00:01:07,835 --> 00:01:10,936
    Lapis, relax.               
It's my communication pad.      

33
00:01:10,938 --> 00:01:12,004
            Who did this to you?

34
00:01:12,006 --> 00:01:13,872
                   Steven,      
      I'll get you out of there.

35
00:01:13,874 --> 00:01:15,707
 Where's your gem on this thing?
             I-I can't find it! 

36
00:01:15,709 --> 00:01:16,775
             Lapis?             

37
00:01:16,777 --> 00:01:18,944
             -What?             
       -He must be inside.      

38
00:01:18,946 --> 00:01:21,046
         -Wait. Lapis --        
      -It's just a screen!      

39
00:01:21,048 --> 00:01:22,881
              Sto--             
           -Oh, geez.           

40
00:01:22,883 --> 00:01:24,216
            [ Pants ]           

41
00:01:24,218 --> 00:01:26,118
Oh, thank the stars.            

42
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,853
I thought you were a goner.     

43
00:01:27,855 --> 00:01:29,455
            Step aside, Peridot.

44
00:01:29,457 --> 00:01:30,956
             I have to free him.

45
00:01:30,958 --> 00:01:32,357
     Lapis, no!                 

46
00:01:32,359 --> 00:01:33,692
               I'll save you,   
                   Steven!      

47
00:01:33,694 --> 00:01:35,594
                I'll save you   
             like you saved me! 

48
00:01:35,596 --> 00:01:37,930
           -Calm down!          
          -Wait! Stop!          

49
00:01:37,932 --> 00:01:39,131
                  I'm fine!     

50
00:01:39,133 --> 00:01:40,232
             Steven!            

51
00:01:40,234 --> 00:01:41,700
          You're okay!          

52
00:01:41,702 --> 00:01:43,535
       Oh, sorry, Peridot.      

53
00:01:43,537 --> 00:01:47,106
     It's okay.                 
Just take it easy with that bat.

54
00:01:47,108 --> 00:01:49,475
            Aw, look. It's Lion.

55
00:01:49,477 --> 00:01:50,709
                W-Wait, Lion.   

56
00:01:50,711 --> 00:01:52,411
              Lion, be careful! 
                  Lion, no!     

57
00:01:52,413 --> 00:01:53,779
            [ Buzz ]            

58
00:01:53,781 --> 00:01:56,748
                     No!        
       That was Connie's laptop!

59
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:58,150
                    Lion!       

60
00:01:58,152 --> 00:02:00,919
He should really be more careful
   with other people's stuff.   

61
00:02:00,921 --> 00:02:02,988
              -Mnh.             
       [ Static squeals ]       

